---
const steps = [
  {
    title: "Write the resolution",
    body:
      "A plan can be as simple as \"No Instagram before breakfast\" or \"Fix the bike before Instagram unlocks.\"",
  },
  {
    title: "Choose the pressure",
    body:
      "PlanKept can schedule reminders and use either a full block or a lighter minute cap for the apps you pick on your iPhone.",
  },
  {
    title: "Do the real thing",
    body:
      "The plan stays active while the action is still undone, so the goal has to move in real life instead of just living in notes.",
  },
  {
    title: "Clear it with proof",
    body:
      "You do not finish by tapping an \"ignore for today\" button. Active plans clear through proof review or accepted justification.",
  },
];
---

<section id="flow" class="landing-section">
  <div class="landing-section__inner">
    <div class="section-heading" data-reveal>
      <p class="section-kicker">How it works</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">A simple flow from intention to follow-through.</h2>
      <p class="section-body">
        PlanKept is not trying to become project management. It takes one plan seriously, applies
        pressure where it matters, and keeps that pressure in place until the plan is actually
        resolved.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="plan-kept-step-grid">
      {steps.map((step, index) => (
        <article class="plan-kept-step landing-surface" data-reveal>
          <p class="plan-kept-step__count">0{index + 1}</p>
          <h3>{step.title}</h3>
          <p>{step.body}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
